### What problem does this feature solve?
Currently `required`, `type` and `validator` properties can be used to validate a prop. I propose an extension that will accept list of validators and possible refactoring of `required` and `type` parameters to simplify the implementation. This way will allow easy reuse of validation logic between components, as you'll be able to easily pass pluggable validators to the prop.

### What does the proposed API look like?

Current way:
    
    Vue.component('my-component', {
      props: {
        propA: {
            type: [Number],
            required: true,
            validator: function(value){
                //Validation logic
                return value > 0;
            }
        }
    })
    
Proposed way:

    function myCustomValidator(){
        //Validation logic
        return (value) => value > 0;
    }

    Vue.component('my-component', {
      props: {
        propA: {
           validators: [
                requiredType([String, Number]),  // Equivalent of `type: [String, Number]`
                isRequired(),                    // Equivalent of `required: true`
                myCustomValidator(),             // Custom validator
          ]
        } 
      }
    })
