### What problem does this feature solve?

#### Background

I am coming from the background of server side and full stack development. Vue is a relatively new passion for me, so please excuse me if this request does not fit well in the Vue's log term vision or if the proposed solution lacks completeness. I have read all GitHub issues that might touch upon the same problem, but none of them was described well or was adding useful business context. 

#### Problem

The business case is that I want to use Vue in the context of a multipage application, where the components used on the page are not known at build time. The decision is taken by content editors via a CMS page builder, which will generate dynamic HTML pages on the fly using the Vue components signatures corresponding to the Props they have modified at Page design time.

As a developer, I want to be able to provide extensibility points on top of Vue, that will allow content editors to choose between different set of predefiend templates for any Vue component that I have provided as a building block for the pages they will manage.

Vue already supports dynamic template compilation and static render functions for performance optimisations. This is part of its core and absolutely love the performance optimisations part of the VNode compilation analysis. The problem is that the internals of Vue that process this functionality are not well documented and or easy to use, so it took me couple of days of digging to find the solution (below).

My goal with reporting this issue is to improve the discoverability of that aspect of Vue, so it becomes a preferred choice for developers building various frameworks on top of Vue. I think, this will also help people develop better UI libraries on top of Vue, such as Vuetify, Bootstrap Vue and etc.. My feeling is that most developers did not found how to enable their UI components to support dynamic templates and improve the extensibility of their UI libraries. 

Here is the code that I developed to deal with it:

``` JavaScript
    export default {
        name: "Error",
        props: {
            templateId: {
                type: String  // templateId gives the address of the template to be used in the form of script tag Id
            },
            heading: {
                type: String
            },
            message: {
                type: String
            }
        },
        render: function (h) {
            let template = document.getElementById(this.templateId);
            if (typeof this.templateId === 'undefined' || template === null)
                return this.renderDefaultTemplate();

            const compiled = Vue.compile(template.innerHTML.trim());
            this.$options.staticRenderFns = [];
            this._staticTrees = [];
            compiled.staticRenderFns.map(fn => (this.$options.staticRenderFns.push(fn)));

            return compiled.render.call(this);
        },
        methods: {
            renderDefaultTemplate: function () {
                // template generated with https://vuejs-tips.github.io/compiler/
                const staticRender = new Function(`with (this) {
            return _c('div', {
                staticClass: "error-message-box"
            }, [_c('div', {
                staticClass: "error-header"
            }, [_c('p', [_v(_s(heading))])]), _c('div', {
                staticClass: "error-main-message"
            }, [_c('p', [_v(_s(message))])])])
        }`);
                return staticRender.call(this);
            }
        }
    };

```

### What does the proposed API look like?
I see 3 possible directions for solution

**Option 1:** if you think that the existing API is adequate, I would love to participate in improving the documentation for the render aspect of Vue.

**Option 2:**  If you like the idea of refactoring current compilation functions in order to expose an easy-to-consume API function for developers, I would love to contribute too.

I am thinking of something that will transform the following lines:

```
  const compiled = Vue.compile(template.innerHTML.trim());
            this.$options.staticRenderFns = [];
            this._staticTrees = [];
            compiled.staticRenderFns.map(fn => (this.$options.staticRenderFns.push(fn)));

            return compiled.render.call(this);
```

to the following lines:

```
            const compiledCode = Vue.compile(template.innerHTML.trim());
            return compiledCode.toVirualNodes(options);
```

**Option 3:** . If you consider this to be more suitable for Vue 3, I would love to contribute there too.

Just let me know on your thoughts of the relevance and value of this for the community and the project and I would love to make it happen!

